sentences: Margaret 'Rita' McAllister (born 6 March 1946) is a Scottish musicologist, composer and academic.
McAllister was born on 6 March 1946 in Mossend, North Lanarkshire.
She studied composition with Anthony Hedges and Robin Orr, and won the first BBC Scotland Young Composerâ€™s prize in 1966.
In the late 1960s she spent three years at the University of Cambridge researching the operas of Sergei Prokofiev; she completed her PhD in 1970.

In the late 1960s she spent three years at the University of Cambridge researching the operas of Sergei Prokofiev; she completed her PhD in 1970.
In the 1970s and 1980s she broadcast and published extensively on many aspects of Soviet and Russian music.

From 1969 she was a lecturer in the Faculty of Music at the University of Edinburgh, teaching composition, 20th-century history and analysis, and established the electronic and recording studios there.
She was appointed Director of Music at the Academy in 1986, and from 1996 to 2006 she was additionally Vice-Principal.
